<h1 id="setup-vendor-master-and-purchase-order-to-be-target-of-consolidated-invoice">Setup vendor master and purchase order to be target of consolidated invoice</h1>


<p>In Japan, the vendors usually use consolidated invoice for transactions.</p>
<p>This task walks you through configuring a vendor master and purchase order to use the consolidated invoice.</p>
<p>This task was created using the demo data company JPMF.</p>
<h2 id="set-up-vendor-master">Set up vendor master</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Accounts payable &gt; Vendors &gt; All vendors.</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li>Expand or collapse the Payment section.
<ul>
<li>Verify that the terms of payment uses the Cutoff day.</li>
<li>Specify a Consolidation day for the vendor.</li>
<li>You might need to click Edit first, before you can update this field.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="set-a-purchase-order-to-be-target-of-consolidated-invoice">Set a purchase order to be target of consolidated invoice</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Accounts payable &gt; Purchase orders &gt; All purchase orders.</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li>On the Action Pane, click Options.</li>
<li>Click Change view.</li>
<li>Click Header view.
<ul>
<li>Verify that the Target of consolidation slider is set to 'Yes'.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
</article>
